# Day 001 - Blink LED using ESP32

## 📅 Date
08 July 2026

## 📌 Project Overview
Today's project is a simple LED Blink program on the ESP32. This is the first step in learning embedded systems and microcontroller programming.

The program configures GPIO pin `T5` as an output and turns the LED ON.

## 🎯 Objective
- Learn GPIO configuration
- Understand digital output
- Set up the ESP32 development environment

## 🛠️ Hardware
- ESP32 Development Board
- LED (or onboard LED)
- USB Cable

## 💻 Software
- Arduino IDE
- ESP32 Board Package

## 📖 What I Learned
- Configuring GPIO pins using `pinMode()`
- Controlling digital outputs with `digitalWrite()`
- Structure of Arduino programs (`setup()` and `loop()`)
